cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper discusses the analysis of user behavior and information propagation on a social multimedia network, which involves social interactions, multimedia content, and user profiles. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), followed by cs.MM (Multimedia), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as they are also relevant to the study of online social networks and multimedia content.
